00:37:50.790 --> 00:37:52.410
over the years is
we're not reliable.

00:37:52.410 --> 00:37:53.710
We come, we go.

00:37:53.710 --> 00:37:55.350
We come in when we
need something.

00:37:55.350 --> 00:37:57.420
As soon as we have
it then we go.

00:37:57.420 --> 00:38:01.890
And in 2004 and 2005 we
were all fighting in Iraq.

00:38:01.890 --> 00:38:04.140
And the Bush administration's
view was

00:38:04.140 --> 00:38:07.440
that Iraq was the main effort
and that Afghanistan was

00:38:07.440 --> 00:38:10.290
at peace and they turned
over security in the country

00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:13.000
to NATO allies and declined

00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:16.590
to resource significant American
commitment to the country.

00:38:16.590 --> 00:38:19.210
And so when the Pakistani
general saw the Dutch coming

00:38:19.210 --> 00:38:22.020
in to provide security
in southern Afghanistan,

00:38:22.020 --> 00:38:25.080
and they saw the American's
concentrating in Iraq,

00:38:25.080 --> 00:38:26.520
they basically said
to themselves

00:38:26.520 --> 00:38:28.420
"So we've seen this
movie before.

00:38:28.420 --> 00:38:29.720
They're, they're going home.

00:38:29.720 --> 00:38:32.630
They're leaving us with this
neighborhood and India's going

00:38:32.630 --> 00:38:35.870
to take advantage of this if
we don't defend our interests."

00:38:35.870 --> 00:38:37.170
That was one reason.

00:38:37.170 --> 00:38:39.000
I think the second
was around this time,

00:38:39.000 --> 00:38:41.400
United States did this
big strategic nuclear deal

00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:42.700
with India.

00:38:42.700 --> 00:38:45.250
India's a natural
21st Century ally

00:38:45.250 --> 00:38:47.200
of the United States
in a lot of ways.

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:50.710
And they wanted India
to, to feel rewarded

00:38:50.710 --> 00:38:52.520
in strategic partnership.

00:38:52.520 --> 00:38:56.020
But they essentially said
to the Indian government,

00:38:56.020 --> 00:38:58.830
