00:42:07.640 --> 00:42:09.690
when he was first
bursting onto the scene.

00:42:09.690 --> 00:42:12.350
He was a very entertaining
person to hang

00:42:12.350 --> 00:42:13.690
around with and write about.

00:42:13.690 --> 00:42:17.920
So if you are interested in him
I -- you can find that online.

00:42:17.920 --> 00:42:21.470
At the time I went back and read
it when he became Prime Minister

00:42:21.470 --> 00:42:24.210
and I was surprised at that time
he really spoke pretty boldly

00:42:24.210 --> 00:42:27.830
about the army which is not
a thing to do in Pakistan

00:42:27.830 --> 00:42:29.300
if you want a political future.

00:42:29.300 --> 00:42:32.780
He was critical of the army
very openly at that time.

00:42:32.780 --> 00:42:34.120
But I think he's seen now

00:42:34.120 --> 00:42:36.910
as having become
partner of the army.

00:42:36.910 --> 00:42:40.750
And the army has -- made
a very clear decision

00:42:40.750 --> 00:42:44.350
and understandable one
that it doesn't want

00:42:44.350 --> 00:42:46.430
to rule Pakistan directly.

00:42:46.430 --> 00:42:49.900
The reputational costs,
the institutional costs,

00:42:49.900 --> 00:42:53.510
the costs in the
international system are high.

00:42:53.510 --> 00:42:57.340
Better to rule indirectly
through civilian politicians

00:42:57.340 --> 00:43:00.590
who can deal with the domestic
problems of the economy

00:43:00.590 --> 00:43:04.520
of negotiating with the
IMF, of all of the problems

00:43:04.520 --> 00:43:06.940
that Pakistan perennially
endures.

00:43:06.940 --> 00:43:11.400
And so Imran Khan I think
has been willing to cooperate

00:43:11.400 --> 00:43:13.020
or to share space with the army.

00:43:13.020 --> 00:43:15.590
You know there're debates
about how much of lackey

00:43:15.590 --> 00:43:18.510
of the army he is, but I think
the record is he's stopped

00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:23.020
criticizing them and he's
accepted their clear kind

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:25.570
of frame work of support
for him to take power.

00:43:25.570 --> 00:43:28.100
Will he be able to
accomplish anything?

00:43:28.100 --> 00:43:30.020
I'm, I'm doubtful.

00:43:30.020 --> 00:43:35.140
And I, I think he might be able
to do a few things domestically,

00:43:35.140 --> 00:43:38.380
particularly with his
anti-corruption drives.

00:43:38.380 --> 00:43:43.080
But in foreign policy clearly
that belongs to the army

00:43:43.080 --> 00:43:45.280
and I don't -- if he tries
to move in that direction --

00:43:45.280 --> 00:43:47.180
every civilian politician
who has tried

00:43:47.180 --> 00:43:51.370
to challenge the army's ideas
about regional policy and,

00:43:51.370 --> 00:43:57.850
and foreign policy has lost
office in a, in a coup or kind

00:43:57.850 --> 00:43:59.860
of indirect electoral coup.

00:43:59.860 --> 00:44:01.160
So he knows that history.

00:44:01.160 --> 00:44:02.810
That goes back 30, 40 years.

